    </StandardHierarchyLevel>
    <StatementCodes>
      <StatementCode>CCSS.Math.Content.7.NS.A.1b</StatementCode>
    </StatementCodes>
    <Statements>
      <Statement>Understand &lt;i&gt;p&lt;/i&gt; + &lt;i&gt;q&lt;/i&gt; as the number located a distance |&lt;i&gt;q&lt;/i&gt;| from &lt;i&gt;p&lt;/i&gt;, in the positive or negative direction depending on whether &lt;i&gt;q&lt;/i&gt; is positive or negative. Show that a number and its opposite have a sum of 0 (are additive inverses). Interpret sums of rational numbers by describing real-world contexts.</Statement>
    </Statements>
